Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%grams} into thirds.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) or use a #garlic press{}.

Quarter the @Lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @Miso Paste{22%grams} and @Honey{15%grams}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for 1
> min to loosen.

Lay the @Salmon Fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined #baking tray{}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, roast the salmon on the top shelf until cooked through,
~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's
> cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, drain the @King Prawns{150%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the prawns, broccoli and @Sugar Snap Peas{80%grams}. Stir-fry for
~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Add the @Yellow Thai Style Paste{45%grams} and @Peanut Butter{30%grams} to the
prawns. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Sweet Chilli Sauce{48%grams}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and
@Water{150%milliliter}(for the sauce). Stir to combine and bring to the boil.

Reduce the heat slightly, then simmer for ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the
> middle.

When the salmon has ~{2%minutes} remaining, remove from the oven and spoon the
miso and honey sauce evenly over each fillet. Return to the oven for the
remaining time.

Meanwhile, add the @Udon Noodles{220%grams} to the frying pan. Toss to coat,
using a #fork{} to gently separate them. Simmer until piping hot,
~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of water if needed.

Remove the pan from the heat and add a good squeeze of lime juice. Taste and
season with salt, pepper and more lime juice if needed.

Share the prawn and udon stir-fry between your serving bowls.

Top with the miso glazed salmon.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!